headlines.description: — Duncan Robinson had five 3-pointers and scored 24 points, Kevin Love provided a big boost off the bench with a season-high 19 points and the Miami Heat overcame a huge game from Charlotte's Terry Rozier to defeat the Hornets 116-114 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Duncan Robinson leads balanced scoring attack as Heat hold on to top Hornets 116-114

headlines.description: — Bennedict Mathurin scored 30 points and the Indiana Pacers handed the Detroit Pistons their 20th straight loss, winning 131-123 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mathurin and Haliburton star as Pacers hand Pistons their 20th straight loss with 131-123 victory

headlines.description: — Orlando's Paolo Banchero had 20 points and 10 rebounds, Franz Wagner scored 19 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers couldn't recover from a dismal third quarter Monday night in a 104-94 loss to the Magic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero, Magic hold Cavaliers to 15 points in 3rd quarter, win 104-94

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid tweaked his left knee in a hard fall last week and needed until the last warmup shot to decide he was healthy enough to play for the 76ers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 34 points, Maxey has 24 in the 76ers' 146-101 beatdown of the Wizards

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 29 points, Nikola Jokic rediscovered his shooting touch to score 25 and the Denver Nuggets ended their three-game skid, holding off the Atlanta Hawks 129-122 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 29, Jokic adds 25 as Nuggets end 3-game skid, beat Bogdanovic, Hawks 129-122

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Facing at least two months without their man in the middle, the New York Knicks showed off the balance they believe can keep them winning without him.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks beat Raptors 136-130 behind a balanced effort in their first game without Robinson

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — On the night the San Antonio Spurs set a franchise record with their 17th consecutive loss, rookie phenom Victor Wembanyama wasn't hanging his head.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets beat Spurs 93-82 and send San Antonio to its franchise-record 17th straight loss

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 35 points, Dereck Lively II added 16 points and 16 rebounds, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Memphis Grizzlies 120-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 35 points, Mavericks beat Grizzlies 120-113 for 3rd straight win

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 32 points and 12 rebounds to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 133-129 victory over the Chicago Bulls in overtime Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo leads Bucks past Bulls 133-129 in OT

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson's road to redemption for his tepid showing in the NBA In-Season Tournament semifinals began against a team with the league's best record.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson's season-high 36 points power Pelicans past Timberwolves, 121-107

events.name: Utah Jazz at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 30 points in three quarters, and the Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Utah Jazz 134-120 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 30 in 3 quarters as Thunder top Jazz 134-120

headlines.description: — DeAaron Fox had 28 points and nine assists, and the Sacramento Kings set a franchise record for 3-pointers with 25 in a 131-118 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings set franchise record for 3s with 25 and beat Nets 131-118

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 34 points and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the short-handed Portland Trail Blazers...
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers hold off short-handed Trail Blazers 132-127 for 4th straight win
